UNDIAGNOSED DISEASE, PORCINE - CHINA: UPDATE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: Fri 5 Jan 2007
From: Dan Silver <dgsilver@yahoo.com>
Source: Xian Evening News [trans. from Chinese by sender, edited]
<http://www.xawb.com/gb/rbpaper/2007-01/05/content_1078703.htm>

The Xian Agricultural Bureau announced on 4 Jan 2007 that "Swine High
Fever Disease" has been brought under control. This disease is not
zoonotic and is not included in the national compulsory vaccination list.
"Swine High Fever Disease" is characterized by high fever, redness of
skin, and respiratory symptoms. The disease is caused by multiple
pathogens and has caused rather large economic losses to the pig
industry. In October 2006, this disease entered Xian through Gaoling
County, spreading to Lintong District, Yanliang District, Weiyang
District, Yanta District, Changan District, Hu County, Zhouzhi County
and 8 other districts and counties, 39 townships and 131 villages. [A
map of the Xian area, in the province Shaanxi, can be seen at
<http://www.chinahighlights.com/xian/map/image/xian-area-map.jpg>].
Total pig stocks in affected villages stood at 13 420 [before the
outbreak]. Disease occurred in 5866 pigs, an incidence rate of 43.7
percent. 2390 pigs died, a mortality rate of 17.8 percent.
After outbreak of the disease, the Xian Agricultural Bureau followed
the spirit of leaders' instructions, repeatedly arranging deployments
and requiring that all districts promptly launch investigations and
surveillance, grasp the situation, and report disease promptly. At
the same time, it launched treatment and implemented safe disposal of
deceased pigs.
Experts repeatedly joined with districts and counties for diagnosis,
prevention and treatment in disease zones. Invitations went to
experts from Shaanxi Animal Husbandry and Veterinary Service,
Northwest Agriculture and Forestry University, the Ministry of
Agriculture's Qingdao Institute of Animal Quarantine and other
research units to conduct dissection, sampling and analysis.
Assistance and guidance was provided to districts and counties for
prevention and control work; prevention and treatment plans were
established and promulgated.
With active adoption of measures by each county and district, this
disease was brought under control in Gaoling, Lintong, Changan, etc.
To prevent this disease from recurring and spreading, the Xian
Agricultural Bureau will take all types of proactive measures,
strengthening the disease fighting ability of pig herds, preventing
purchase and sale of diseased pigs and pork products and strictly
preventing diseased, dead pigs and their products from entering the
commercial realm.
[Byline: Xun Han]
--
Dan Silver
<dgsilver@yahoo.com>
