[2]
Date: Fri 5 Jan 2007
From: Dan Silver <dgsilver@yahoo.com>
Source: Wehai Mayor's Public Helpline [trans. from Chinese by sender, edited]
<http://www.weihai.gov.cn/12345/default.asp?id=73225>

Regarding the Question of Diseased Swine
-----------------------------------------------
Telephone inquiry:
Is there truth to the rumor that many pigs are ill in the cities of
Rongcheng, Wendeng, and Rushan? Can pork on the market be consumed
with confidence? A response is requested from the appropriate department.
The Animal Husbandry Bureau's reply:
From the latter part of October 2006, swine disease entered the
municipality from outside, causing pigs in some of our towns and
villages to fall ill. All municipal animal husbandry and veterinary
agencies viewed the situation with seriousness, undertaking cleaning,
isolation, symptomatic treatment, quarantine supervision and other
work. The disease has already been brought under effective control.
Marketed pork has undergone inspection and can be consumed with confidence.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The said locations are in the province Shandong. - Mod.AS]
